      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on this embedded c++ project for a car ECU and i've got a memory leak issue. the system just slowly runs out of ram after like 4 or 5 hours of running. i can't really use heavy tools like valgrind because of the hardware constraints. i'll post a snippet of the main loop and the allocation logic below. can u give me a systematic way to find where the leak is happening? \n\nhere is the code:\n\n```cpp\nvoid process_sensor_data() {\n    SensorData* data = new SensorData();\n    data->timestamp = get_time();\n    data->value = read_adc();\n\n    if (data->value > THRESHOLD) {\n        handle_alert(data); \n    }\n    \n    // logic to queue data for logging\n    log_queue.push(data);\n}\n\nvoid handle_alert(SensorData* d) {\n    // some logic...\n    // sometimes we process it and forget to free it if it's a duplicate?\n    if (is_duplicate(d)) {\n        return; \n    }\n    process_detailed_log(d);\n}\n```",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
