      "content": "yeah, you're probably right about the duplicate check. if is_duplicate is true, it just returns and that pointer is lost. \n\nbut even with that fix, i'm still seeing some weirdness. i've been trying to trace the pointers manually and it's like some memory just vanishes into thin air without any obvious reason. it's super hard to catch because it's so slow and subtle. do you have any other ideas for finding these \"invisible\" leaks that aren't just obvious missing deletes?",
